The paper focuses on developing a new CNN architecture for medical image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of different activation functions to improve classification performance, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of reducing memory usage and computational power for building effective healthcare systems, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
